HEADWORD: Home-bred
<hw>Home"-bred`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Bred
at home; domestic; not foreign.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧ <xex>Home-bred</xex>
mischief.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Benignity and <qex>home-bred</qex> sense.</q>
<rj><qau>Wordsworth.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Not polished; rude; uncultivated.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Only to me <qex>home-bred</qex> youths belong.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

